{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JYo2JxDqTqE3irmVM3gfRU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→version: 5\n     3→title: \"AI-Native Software Development\"\n     4→subtitle: \"Building the Future of Code\"\n     5→author: \"Jane Developer\"\n     6→event: \"TechConf 2026\"\n     7→date: \"2026-03-15\"\n     8→target_minutes: 15\n     9→audio_voice: \"af_heart\"\n    10→\n    11→branding:\n    12→  primary: \"#2563eb\"\n    13→  background: \"#1e1e2e\"\n    14→  text: \"#f8fafc\"\n    15→\n    16→sections:\n    17→  - id: opening\n    18→    name: \"Opening\"\n    19→    color: \"#557373\"\n    20→  - id: problem\n    21→    name: \"The Problem\"\n    22→    color: \"#6B4C4C\"\n    23→  - id: solution\n    24→    name: \"Our Solution\"\n    25→    color: \"#4C6B5D\"\n    26→  - id: closing\n    27→    name: \"Closing\"\n    28→    color: \"#5D4C6B\"\n    29→  - id: appendix\n    30→    name: \"Appendix\"\n    31→    color: \"#666666\"\n    32→---\n    33→\n    34→## Slides\n    35→\n    36→| # | Slug | Title | Image | Section |\n    37→|---|------|-------|-------|---------|\n    38→| 1 | title-slide | Welcome to AI-Native Dev | slide-01-title.png | opening |\n    39→| 2 | hook-problem | The Current State | slide-02-hook.png | problem |\n    40→| 3 | evidence-stats | By the Numbers | slide-03-stats.png | problem |\n    41→| 4 | solution-intro | A New Approach | slide-04-solution.png | solution |\n    42→| 5 | demo-walkthrough | See It In Action | slide-05-demo.png | solution |\n    43→| 6 | call-to-action | Get Started Today | slide-06-cta.png | closing |\n    44→| A1 | appendix-resources | Additional Resources | slide-a1-resources.png | appendix |\n    45→\n    46→## [title-slide] Welcome to AI-Native Dev\n    47→\n    48→![Title](images/slide-01-title.png)\n    49→\n    50→<!-- AUDIO -->\n    51→[HOOK] What if writing code felt less like fighting with syntax and more like having a conversation with a brilliant collaborator?\n    52→\n    53→Welcome everyone. I'm Jane Developer, and today we're going to explore how AI is fundamentally changing the way we build software.\n    54→\n    55→[PAUSE:500]\n    56→\n    57→This isn't about AI replacing developers. It's about AI amplifying what developers can do.\n    58→<!-- /AUDIO -->\n    59→\n    60→**Speaker Notes:**\n    61→- Make eye contact with the audience\n    62→- Gauge the room's technical level\n    63→- Pause for effect after the hook\n    64→\n    65→---\n    66→\n    67→## [hook-problem] The Current State\n    68→\n    69→![The Problem](images/slide-02-hook.png)\n    70→\n    71→<!-- AUDIO -->\n    72→[TRANSITION] But first, let's talk about where we are today.\n    73→\n    74→The software development landscape is facing unprecedented challenges.\n    75→\n    76→[KEY_POINT] Development cycles are getting shorter while complexity is increasing exponentially.\n    77→\n    78→Teams are expected to deliver more features, faster, with fewer bugs. And the tools we've been using for decades are struggling to keep up.\n    79→\n    80→[PAUSE:300]\n    81→\n    82→Sound familiar?\n    83→<!-- /AUDIO -->\n    84→\n    85→**Speaker Notes:**\n    86→- Rhetorical question to engage audience\n    87→- Let the statistics on the next slide speak for themselves\n    88→\n    89→---\n    90→\n    91→## [evidence-stats] By the Numbers\n    92→\n    93→![Statistics](images/slide-03-stats.png)\n    94→\n    95→<!-- AUDIO -->\n    96→[EVIDENCE] Let me share some data that might surprise you.\n    97→\n    98→According to recent studies, developers spend only 30% of their time actually writing new code. The rest goes to debugging, reading documentation, and context switching.\n    99→\n   100→[KEY_POINT] That's 70% of our working hours on tasks that don't directly add value.\n   101→\n   102→[PAUSE:400]\n   103→\n   104→Imagine if we could reclaim even half of that time.\n   105→<!-- /AUDIO -->\n   106→\n   107→**Speaker Notes:**\n   108→- Source: Stack Overflow Developer Survey 2025\n   109→- GitHub State of Octoverse report\n   110→- These numbers resonate with most developers\n   111→\n   112→---\n   113→\n   114→## [solution-intro] A New Approach\n   115→\n   116→![Solution](images/slide-04-solution.png)\n   117→\n   118→<!-- AUDIO -->\n   119→[TRANSITION] Now let's talk about how AI-native development changes everything.\n   120→\n   121→[KEY_POINT] AI-native development isn't about bolting AI onto existing workflows. It's about reimagining the development process from the ground up.\n   122→\n   123→When AI understands your codebase, your intent, and your patterns, it becomes a true force multiplier.\n   124→\n   125→[STORY] One team I worked with reduced their time-to-production by 40% after adopting AI-native practices.\n   126→\n   127→They didn't work longer hours. They worked smarter.\n   128→<!-- /AUDIO -->\n   129→\n   130→**Speaker Notes:**\n   131→- Emphasize the word \"reimagining\"\n   132→- The story is from Acme Corp (anonymized)\n   133→\n   134→---\n   135→\n   136→## [demo-walkthrough] See It In Action\n   137→\n   138→![Demo](images/slide-05-demo.png)\n   139→\n   140→<!-- AUDIO -->\n   141→Let me show you what this looks like in practice.\n   142→\n   143→[PAUSE:300]\n   144→\n   145→Watch as I describe what I want to build, and the AI collaborates with me in real-time.\n   146→\n   147→[KEY_POINT] Notice how I'm not fighting with syntax. I'm describing intent.\n   148→\n   149→The AI handles the boilerplate while I focus on the logic that matters.\n   150→\n   151→[CALLBACK] Remember that 70% of time we talked about earlier? This is how we reclaim it.\n   152→<!-- /AUDIO -->\n   153→\n   154→**Speaker Notes:**\n   155→- Live demo section - have backup video ready\n   156→- Highlight the natural language interface\n   157→- Show error correction in action\n   158→\n   159→---\n   160→\n   161→## [call-to-action] Get Started Today\n   162→\n   163→![Call to Action](images/slide-06-cta.png)\n   164→\n   165→<!-- AUDIO -->\n   166→[LANDING] So where do we go from here?\n   167→\n   168→[CTA] I want you to try one thing this week. Take your most tedious coding task and see if an AI assistant can help.\n   169→\n   170→Start small. Build confidence. Then expand.\n   171→\n   172→[PAUSE:500]\n   173→\n   174→The future of software development isn't about AI versus humans.\n   175→\n   176→It's about what humans can accomplish when AI has their back.\n   177→\n   178→Thank you.\n   179→<!-- /AUDIO -->\n   180→\n   181→**Speaker Notes:**\n   182→- Strong close - make eye contact\n   183→- Leave time for questions\n   184→- Have QR code ready for resources\n   185→\n   186→---\n   187→\n   188→## [appendix-resources] Additional Resources\n   189→\n   190→![Resources](images/slide-a1-resources.png)\n   191→\n   192→<!-- AUDIO -->\n   193→[TRANSITION] For those who want to dive deeper, here are some resources.\n   194→\n   195→We've put together a comprehensive guide covering best practices, tool recommendations, and case studies.\n   196→\n   197→All links are available in the presentation materials you'll receive after this session.\n   198→<!-- /AUDIO -->\n   199→\n   200→**Speaker Notes:**\n   201→- Only show if asked about resources\n   202→- QR code links to resource hub\n   203→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01NSueNmmedTxDHb613XuvtJ","session_id":"fae97709-6dbb-4c53-abde-6088a81b1e30","uuid":"0f96e36c-3ad5-4c73-8313-c8d68432d09c"}
