{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EF123SaS5Cbe2NhjtnAj4D","type":"tool_result","content":"2159-        <div class=\"pv-current\">\n2160-            <h3>Current Slide</h3>\n2161:            <img id=\"pvCurrent\" src=\"\">\n2162-            <div class=\"pv-timer\" id=\"pvTimer\">00:00</div>\n2163-        </div>\n--\n2165-            <div class=\"pv-next\">\n2166-                <h3>Next Slide</h3>\n2167:                <img id=\"pvNext\" src=\"\">\n2168-            </div>\n2169-            <div class=\"pv-notes\">\n--\n2578-  const filmstripItems = slides.map((slide, index) => `\n2579-            <div class=\"filmstrip-item${index === 0 ? ' current' : ''}\" data-index=\"${index}\" onclick=\"goToSlide(${index})\">\n2580:                <img src=\"${escapeHtml(slide.imagePath)}\" alt=\"${escapeHtml(slide.title)}\" loading=\"lazy\">\n2581-                <div class=\"filmstrip-item-label\">${index + 1}</div>\n2582-            </div>`).join('');\n--\n2596-  const gridItems = slides.map((slide, index) => `\n2597-        <div class=\"grid-item${index === 0 ? ' current' : ''}\" data-index=\"${index}\" onclick=\"goToSlideFromGrid(${index})\">\n2598:            <img src=\"${escapeHtml(slide.imagePath)}\" alt=\"${escapeHtml(slide.title)}\" loading=\"lazy\">\n2599-            <div class=\"grid-item-info\">\n2600-                <div class=\"grid-item-number\">${index + 1}</div>\n--\n2745-    <div class=\"presentation\">\n2746-        <div class=\"slide-container\">\n2747:            <img class=\"slide\" id=\"currentSlide\" src=\"\" alt=\"Slide\">\n2748-        </div>\n2749-"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01CxjStoqz4pfoTiMxyQouKJ","session_id":"fae97709-6dbb-4c53-abde-6088a81b1e30","uuid":"645954bb-6681-4bfc-aa1d-4d722cbff894"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NSueNmmedTxDHb613XuvtJ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now I have all the information I need. Let me trace through the logic to understand the caption sync failure:\n\n## Analysis & Findings\n\nBased on my review of the code and test setup, I've identified the root cause of the `timeline.slides.find((s) => s.captions.length > 0)` returning `undefined`.\n\n### The Issue\n\nThe test assumes that **all slides will have captions**, but the current implementation only generates captions when `wordTimings` are available. This is a **test setup issue**, not a code bug.\n\n### Root Cause Chain\n\n1. **Mock Audio Manifest Creation** (`tests/integration/timeline.test.ts`, lines 51-76)\n   - The `createMockAudioManifest()` function creates `AudioManifestEntry` objects with `duration` but **never includes `wordTimings`**\n   - It only sets these fields: `slug`, `path`, `duration`, `provider`\n   - Missing: `wordTimings?: WordTiming[]`\n\n2. **buildCaptions Logic** (`src/generators/timeline/index.ts`, lines 229-237)\n   ```typescript\n   function buildCaptions(text: string, audioEntry: AudioManifestEntry): Caption[] {\n     if (audioEntry.wordTimings && audioEntry.wordTimings.length > 0) {\n       // Use Whisper word timings directly\n       return buildCaptionsFromWordTimings(audioEntry.wordTimings);\n     }\n     \n     // No word timings (Kokoro without Whisper) - skip captions entirely\n     return [];  // <-- RETURNS EMPTY ARRAY\n   }\n   ```\n\n3. **Why captions are empty**\n   - The mock audio manifest uses `provider: 'kokoro'` (line 67 of test)\n   - Kokoro is a local TTS that doesn't provide word-level timings\n   - The implementation explicitly **skips caption generation for Kokoro without Whisper** (intentional design decision per the comment on line 235)\n   - No code calls the caption estimation functions (`estimateCaptionTimings`, `scaleCaptionsToAudioDuration`) during timeline building\n\n### Test Expectations vs. Reality\n\nThe test at line 182 expects:\n```typescript\nconst slideWithCaptions = timeline.slides.find((s) => s.captions.length > 0);\nexpect(slideWithCaptions).toBeDefined();  // <-- FAILS\n```\n\nBut every slide gets an empty `captions` array because:\n- All mock audio entries lack `wordTimings`\n- The code only generates captions from `wordTimings` or returns `[]`\n- No fallback caption estimation is invoked during `buildTimeline()`\n\n### Design Context\n\nThis is intentional per the comments in `src/generators/timeline/index.ts` (lines 227-237):\n> \"Returns empty array if no word timings - Kokoro without Whisper gets no captions.\"\n\nThe codebase distinguishes between:\n- **ElevenLabs + Whisper**: Provides word-level timings → generates precise captions\n- **Kokoro (local TTS)**: No word timings → skips captions (returns `[]`)\n\nThe `estimateCaptionTimings()` and `scaleCaptionsToAudioDuration()` functions exist but are **only exported for utility tests** (lines 221-229 of the test file), not used in actual timeline building.\n\n### Summary\n\n**Test Issue**: The mock setup doesn't simulate the two caption generation scenarios:\n1. ElevenLabs with word timings (has captions)\n2. Kokoro without word timings (no captions)\n\nTo fix the test, either:\n- Add mock `wordTimings` to make captions generate\n- Update the test assertions to handle the no-captions scenario\n- Refactor caption generation to estimate timings for Kokoro (separate issue)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a584cc08768ffde30 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 107087\ntool_uses: 6\nduration_ms: 17217</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fae97709-6dbb-4c53-abde-6088a81b1e30","uuid":"fbfaf9ad-2a96-4d00-86e3-11cfc307c4dd","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the timeline caption sync test failure in PresentationKit.\n\n1. Read `tests/integration/timeline.test.ts` from the beginning to understand how the timeline is constructed for tests (what fixture data, what mock data)\n2. Look at `src/generators/timeline/` to understand how captions are generated and under what conditions captions would be empty\n3. Determine: Why would `timeline.slides.find((s) => s.captions.length > 0)` return `undefined`? Is it a test setup issue or a code change that broke caption generation?\n\nReport back with your findings.","agentId":"a584cc08768ffde30","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now I have all the information I need. Let me trace through the logic to understand the caption sync failure:\n\n## Analysis & Findings\n\nBased on my review of the code and test setup, I've identified the root cause of the `timeline.slides.find((s) => s.captions.length > 0)` returning `undefined`.\n\n### The Issue\n\nThe test assumes that **all slides will have captions**, but the current implementation only generates captions when `wordTimings` are available. This is a **test setup issue**, not a code bug.\n\n### Root Cause Chain\n\n1. **Mock Audio Manifest Creation** (`tests/integration/timeline.test.ts`, lines 51-76)\n   - The `createMockAudioManifest()` function creates `AudioManifestEntry` objects with `duration` but **never includes `wordTimings`**\n   - It only sets these fields: `slug`, `path`, `duration`, `provider`\n   - Missing: `wordTimings?: WordTiming[]`\n\n2. **buildCaptions Logic** (`src/generators/timeline/index.ts`, lines 229-237)\n   ```typescript\n   function buildCaptions(text: string, audioEntry: AudioManifestEntry): Caption[] {\n     if (audioEntry.wordTimings && audioEntry.wordTimings.length > 0) {\n       // Use Whisper word timings directly\n       return buildCaptionsFromWordTimings(audioEntry.wordTimings);\n     }\n     \n     // No word timings (Kokoro without Whisper) - skip captions entirely\n     return [];  // <-- RETURNS EMPTY ARRAY\n   }\n   ```\n\n3. **Why captions are empty**\n   - The mock audio manifest uses `provider: 'kokoro'` (line 67 of test)\n   - Kokoro is a local TTS that doesn't provide word-level timings\n   - The implementation explicitly **skips caption generation for Kokoro without Whisper** (intentional design decision per the comment on line 235)\n   - No code calls the caption estimation functions (`estimateCaptionTimings`, `scaleCaptionsToAudioDuration`) during timeline building\n\n### Test Expectations vs. Reality\n\nThe test at line 182 expects:\n```typescript\nconst slideWithCaptions = timeline.slides.find((s) => s.captions.length > 0);\nexpect(slideWithCaptions).toBeDefined();  // <-- FAILS\n```\n\nBut every slide gets an empty `captions` array because:\n- All mock audio entries lack `wordTimings`\n- The code only generates captions from `wordTimings` or returns `[]`\n- No fallback caption estimation is invoked during `buildTimeline()`\n\n### Design Context\n\nThis is intentional per the comments in `src/generators/timeline/index.ts` (lines 227-237):\n> \"Returns empty array if no word timings - Kokoro without Whisper gets no captions.\"\n\nThe codebase distinguishes between:\n- **ElevenLabs + Whisper**: Provides word-level timings → generates precise captions\n- **Kokoro (local TTS)**: No word timings → skips captions (returns `[]`)\n\nThe `estimateCaptionTimings()` and `scaleCaptionsToAudioDuration()` functions exist but are **only exported for utility tests** (lines 221-229 of the test file), not used in actual timeline building.\n\n### Summary\n\n**Test Issue**: The mock setup doesn't simulate the two caption generation scenarios:\n1. ElevenLabs with word timings (has captions)\n2. Kokoro without word timings (no captions)\n\nTo fix the test, either:\n- Add mock `wordTimings` to make captions generate\n- Update the test assertions to handle the no-captions scenario\n- Refactor caption generation to estimate timings for Kokoro (separate issue)"}],"totalDurationMs":17217,"totalTokens":107087,"totalToolUseCount":6,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,