{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CxjStoqz4pfoTiMxyQouKJ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a summary report:\n\n## HTML Renderer Accessibility Issue - Investigation Report\n\n**Status:** The `<img>` tags at lines 2161 and 2167 in the HTML renderer are **missing `alt` attributes**.\n\n### Failing Test Details\n- **File:** `/Users/leegonzales/Projects/leegonzales/PresentationKit/tests/integration/html-renderer.test.ts`\n- **Test:** Lines 339-345, in the \"HTML Renderer Integration: Accessibility\" describe block\n- **What it checks:** All `<img>` tags in the generated HTML must have an `alt` attribute\n- **Test code:**\n  ```typescript\n  it('should include alt text for images', () => {\n    // Images should have alt attributes\n    const imgTags = htmlOutputWithTimeline.match(/<img[^>]+>/g) || [];\n    for (const img of imgTags) {\n      expect(img).toContain('alt=');\n    }\n  });\n  ```\n\n### Problem Locations in Source Code\n\n**File:** `/Users/leegonzales/Projects/leegonzales/PresentationKit/src/renderers/html/template.ts`\n\nThree `<img>` tags need fixes:\n\n1. **Line 2161** (Speaker view - Current Slide):\n   ```html\n   <img id=\"pvCurrent\" src=\"\">\n   <!-- Missing alt attribute -->\n   ```\n\n2. **Line 2167** (Speaker view - Next Slide):\n   ```html\n   <img id=\"pvNext\" src=\"\">\n   <!-- Missing alt attribute -->\n   ```\n\n3. **Line 2747** (Main presentation view):\n   ```html\n   <img class=\"slide\" id=\"currentSlide\" src=\"\" alt=\"Slide\">\n   <!-- This one ALREADY HAS alt attribute -->\n   ```\n\n### Comparison with Correct Implementation\nThe filmstrip and grid views (lines 2580 and 2598) correctly include alt attributes:\n```html\n<img src=\"${escapeHtml(slide.imagePath)}\" alt=\"${escapeHtml(slide.title)}\" loading=\"lazy\">\n```\n\n### Fix Required\nAdd `alt` attributes to the two missing `<img>` tags in the speaker view section:\n\n- **Line 2161:** Change `<img id=\"pvCurrent\" src=\"\">` to `<img id=\"pvCurrent\" src=\"\" alt=\"Current slide\">`\n- **Line 2167:** Change `<img id=\"pvNext\" src=\"\">` to `<img id=\"pvNext\" src=\"\" alt=\"Next slide\">`\n\nThe alt text should be descriptive but concise, matching the pattern used in the rest of the codebase."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ac8d2e69ab6393b9d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 102982\ntool_uses: 11\nduration_ms: 28462</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fae97709-6dbb-4c53-abde-6088a81b1e30","uuid":"0689ff7d-3fed-4084-bf44-2b185c8fc208","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the HTML renderer accessibility issue in PresentationKit.\n\n1. Read the failing test at `tests/integration/html-renderer.test.ts`, specifically around line 340-350, to understand what it checks\n2. Read the HTML renderer source code in `src/renderers/html/` to find where `<img>` tags are generated, particularly the one with `id=\"pvCurrent\"`\n3. Determine: Is the `alt` attribute missing from `<img>` tags in the HTML renderer output? Where exactly is the img tag generated?\n\nReport back with the specific file, line, and what the fix would need to be.","agentId":"ac8d2e69ab6393b9d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a summary report:\n\n## HTML Renderer Accessibility Issue - Investigation Report\n\n**Status:** The `<img>` tags at lines 2161 and 2167 in the HTML renderer are **missing `alt` attributes**.\n\n### Failing Test Details\n- **File:** `/Users/leegonzales/Projects/leegonzales/PresentationKit/tests/integration/html-renderer.test.ts`\n- **Test:** Lines 339-345, in the \"HTML Renderer Integration: Accessibility\" describe block\n- **What it checks:** All `<img>` tags in the generated HTML must have an `alt` attribute\n- **Test code:**\n  ```typescript\n  it('should include alt text for images', () => {\n    // Images should have alt attributes\n    const imgTags = htmlOutputWithTimeline.match(/<img[^>]+>/g) || [];\n    for (const img of imgTags) {\n      expect(img).toContain('alt=');\n    }\n  });\n  ```\n\n### Problem Locations in Source Code\n\n**File:** `/Users/leegonzales/Projects/leegonzales/PresentationKit/src/renderers/html/template.ts`\n\nThree `<img>` tags need fixes:\n\n1. **Line 2161** (Speaker view - Current Slide):\n   ```html\n   <img id=\"pvCurrent\" src=\"\">\n   <!-- Missing alt attribute -->\n   ```\n\n2. **Line 2167** (Speaker view - Next Slide):\n   ```html\n   <img id=\"pvNext\" src=\"\">\n   <!-- Missing alt attribute -->\n   ```\n\n3. **Line 2747** (Main presentation view):\n   ```html\n   <img class=\"slide\" id=\"currentSlide\" src=\"\" alt=\"Slide\">\n   <!-- This one ALREADY HAS alt attribute -->\n   ```\n\n### Comparison with Correct Implementation\nThe filmstrip and grid views (lines 2580 and 2598) correctly include alt attributes:\n```html\n<img src=\"${escapeHtml(slide.imagePath)}\" alt=\"${escapeHtml(slide.title)}\" loading=\"lazy\">\n```\n\n### Fix Required\nAdd `alt` attributes to the two missing `<img>` tags in the speaker view section:\n\n- **Line 2161:** Change `<img id=\"pvCurrent\" src=\"\">` to `<img id=\"pvCurrent\" src=\"\" alt=\"Current slide\">`\n- **Line 2167:** Change `<img id=\"pvNext\" src=\"\">` to `<img id=\"pvNext\" src=\"\" alt=\"Next slide\">`\n\nThe alt text should be descriptive but concise, matching the pattern used in the rest of the codebase."}],"totalDurationMs":28462,"totalTokens":102982,"totalToolUseCount":11,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":334,"cache_read_input_tokens":102007,"output_tokens":640,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":334},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Hv4DasBDFoVNnhH6QmfxmU","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me create a summary document with my findings:\n\n## Summary: Image Path Normalization in PresentationKit\n\nBased on my analysis of the codebase, git history, and tests, here are my findings:\n\n### Key Facts\n\n**1. The `normalizeImagePath()` function was added in commit `7c4b213` (Jan 24, 2026)**\n\nThis function normalizes image paths to ensure a consistent `images/` prefix across the parser. It handles various input formats:\n- `slide.png` → `images/slide.png` (adds prefix)\n- `images/slide.png` → `images/slide.png` (already normalized, unchanged)\n- `./images/slide.png` → `images/slide.png` (removes `./`)\n- `../assets/slide.png` → `../assets/slide.png` (external paths unchanged)\n- `/absolute/path.png` → `/absolute/path.png` (absolute paths unchanged)\n- `http://...` → `http://...` (URLs unchanged)\n\n**2. Image paths are normalized in TWO places:**\n\n- **Slides table parsing** (line 193 in `src/parsers/talk-track.ts`):\n  - Normalizes the image column from the `## Slides` table\n  \n- **Slide content parsing** (line 352 in `src/parsers/talk-track.ts`):\n  - Normalizes images extracted from markdown `![](...)` syntax in slide content sections\n\n**3. The intent is INTENTIONAL and DOCUMENTED**\n\nThe commit message states:\n- \"Add normalizeImagePath() to ensure consistent images/ prefix\"\n- \"Normalize image paths from both slides table and content sections\"\n- Fixes issue PresentationKit-lzz (\"mixed image path formats\")\n\n### Test Expectations\n\nLooking at the test files:\n\n**In `tests/talk-track.test.ts` (line 250):**\n```typescript\nimage: 'slide-title.png',  // Expected: NO images/ prefix in slides table\n```\n\n**In `tests/integration/parser.test.ts` (line 133):**\n```typescript\nexpect(titleSlide?.image).toBe('slide-01-title.png');  // Expected: NO images/ prefix\n```\n\n**But in `tests/integration/parser.test.ts` (line 185):**\n```typescript\nexpect(hookContent?.imagePath).toBe('images/slide-02-hook.png');  // Expected: WITH images/ prefix\n```\n\n### Critical Distinction: `image` vs `imagePath`\n\nThe parser returns TWO different properties:\n\n1. **`slide.image`** - From the slides table, stores the **raw/normalized plain filename** (e.g., `slide-01-title.png`)\n2. **`slideContent.imagePath`** - From the slide content sections, stores the **full normalized path with `images/` prefix** (e.g., `images/slide-01-title.png`)\n\nThe test fixture (`tests/fixtures/sample-talk-track.md`) confirms this:\n- **Slides table (line 38)**: `slide-01-title.png` (no prefix)\n- **Content section (line 48)**: `![Title](images/slide-01-title.png)` (with prefix)\n\n### Conclusion\n\n**YES, the `images/` prefix is intentional.** Here's the behavior:\n\n1. **When normalizing table images**: If a user writes `slide.png` or `./images/slide.png` in the table, it gets normalized to `images/slide.png` in the `image` property\n2. **When parsing content images**: If a user writes `![](slide.png)` or `![](images/slide.png)` in the markdown, it gets normalized to `images/slide.png` in the `imagePath` property\n3. **Consistency goal**: Handle both \"lazy\" paths (plain filenames) and explicit paths, normalizing to a standard format\n\n**Tests should expect:**\n- `slides[].image`: Plain normalized filename (e.g., `slide-01-title.png`)\n- `slideContent[slug].imagePath`: Full path with prefix (e.g., `images/slide-01-title.png`)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a60ff88f4778cac37 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 111003\ntool_uses: 10\nduration_ms: 32366</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fae97709-6dbb-4c53-abde-6088a81b1e30","uuid":"608d85ab-0246-42de-ad1f-4e1d1ecea03f","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the image path normalization behavior in PresentationKit's parser.\n\n1. Look at `src/parsers/` for any function that handles image paths, particularly looking for where `images/` prefix is added\n2. Check the git diff for commit `7c4b213` to see what changed: `git show 7c4b213 --stat` and then `git show 7c4b213` for the full diff\n3. Read the test fixture file used by the parser tests - look in `tests/fixtures/` for any Talk Track markdown files\n4. Determine: Is the `images/` prefix on image paths intentional? Should tests expect `images/slide-01-title.png` or `slide-01-title.png`?\n\nReport back with your findings.","agentId":"a60ff88f4778cac37","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me create a summary document with my findings:\n\n## Summary: Image Path Normalization in PresentationKit\n\nBased on my analysis of the codebase, git history, and tests, here are my findings:\n\n### Key Facts\n\n**1. The `normalizeImagePath()` function was added in commit `7c4b213` (Jan 24, 2026)**\n\nThis function normalizes image paths to ensure a consistent `images/` prefix across the parser. It handles various input formats:\n- `slide.png` → `images/slide.png` (adds prefix)\n- `images/slide.png` → `images/slide.png` (already normalized, unchanged)\n- `./images/slide.png` → `images/slide.png` (removes `./`)\n- `../assets/slide.png` → `../assets/slide.png` (external paths unchanged)\n- `/absolute/path.png` → `/absolute/path.png` (absolute paths unchanged)\n- `http://...` → `http://...` (URLs unchanged)\n\n**2. Image paths are normalized in TWO places:**\n\n- **Slides table parsing** (line 193 in `src/parsers/talk-track.ts`):\n  - Normalizes the image column from the `## Slides` table\n  \n- **Slide content parsing** (line 352 in `src/parsers/talk-track.ts`):\n  - Normalizes images extracted from markdown `![](...)` syntax in slide content sections\n\n**3. The intent is INTENTIONAL and DOCUMENTED**\n\nThe commit message states:\n- \"Add normalizeImagePath() to ensure consistent images/ prefix\"\n- \"Normalize image paths from both slides table and content sections\"\n- Fixes issue PresentationKit-lzz (\"mixed image path formats\")\n\n### Test Expectations\n\nLooking at the test files:\n\n**In `tests/talk-track.test.ts` (line 250):**\n```typescript\nimage: 'slide-title.png',  // Expected: NO images/ prefix in slides table\n```\n\n**In `tests/integration/parser.test.ts` (line 133):**\n```typescript\nexpect(titleSlide?.image).toBe('slide-01-title.png');  // Expected: NO images/ prefix\n```\n\n**But in `tests/integration/parser.test.ts` (line 185):**\n```typescript\nexpect(hookContent?.imagePath).toBe('images/slide-02-hook.png');  // Expected: WITH images/ prefix\n```\n\n### Critical Distinction: `image` vs `imagePath`\n\nThe parser returns TWO different properties:\n\n1. **`slide.image`** - From the slides table, stores the **raw/normalized plain filename** (e.g., `slide-01-title.png`)\n2. **`slideContent.imagePath`** - From the slide content sections, stores the **full normalized path with `images/` prefix** (e.g., `images/slide-01-title.png`)\n\nThe test fixture (`tests/fixtures/sample-talk-track.md`) confirms this:\n- **Slides table (line 38)**: `slide-01-title.png` (no prefix)\n- **Content section (line 48)**: `![Title](images/slide-01-title.png)` (with prefix)\n\n### Conclusion\n\n**YES, the `images/` prefix is intentional.** Here's the behavior:\n\n1. **When normalizing table images**: If a user writes `slide.png` or `./images/slide.png` in the table, it gets normalized to `images/slide.png` in the `image` property\n2. **When parsing content images**: If a user writes `![](slide.png)` or `![](images/slide.png)` in the markdown, it gets normalized to `images/slide.png` in the `imagePath` property\n3. **Consistency goal**: Handle both \"lazy\" paths (plain filenames) and explicit paths, normalizing to a standard format\n\n**Tests should expect:**\n- `slides[].image`: Plain normalized filename (e.g., `slide-01-title.png`)\n- `slideContent[slug].imagePath`: Full path with prefix (e.g., `images/slide-01-title.png`)"}],"totalDurationMs":32366,"totalTokens":111003,"totalToolUseCount":10,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":150,"cache_read_input_tokens":109862,"output_tokens":991,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":150},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
